To receive a G.- visitation card (also known as GPV card), individuals must meet certain eligibility criteria. Specifically, those meeting any of these conditions are eligible:
- A person is between the ages of zero and seven years old;
- They are sixty years or older; 
- Someone qualifies for carer's benefit or allowance at either the full rate or partial rate;
For persons under seventy, there is no financial assessment done. However for anyone else, a means-tested assessment is conducted by H.S.E., which determines whether or not they qualify. Document 4:::

